                  </objectDesc>
                  
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>One excellent anglicana formata, probably by a Continental scribe (alternating Continental and English g). The scribe is probably responsible for the foliation, running heads and marginal chapter numbers.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>On <locus>f. 1</locus> an 8-line D, red and blue on a ground of red flourishing and with 2-sided border in the colours; blue initials flourished in red.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="1600" notAfter="1700">
                        <p> Standard Merton s.
               xvii, repaired and rebacked; sewn on nine bands; formerly chained from the foredge of
               the front board near the foot. Fols. i, 227-8 are paper binding leaves, f. 228 from the
               same book as in MS 84. f. 226, formerly a pastedown in an earlier binding, has the
               marks of two strap-pins, and of the large ?brass chain-staple near the foot.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
